{"title":"Macworld Podcast: Your hot takes about the Mac, iPad mini, and more","link":"https://www.macworld.com/article/2553704/hot-takes-mac-ipad-mini-macworld-podcast.html","date":1735805700000,"content":"<p><a href=\"https://www.macworld.com\">Macworld</a></p>\n\n<div>\n<section><div></div></section>\n\n\n\n<p>On this week‚Äôs episode of the Macworld Podcast, it‚Äôs all about your hot takes! You have thoughts about the iMac, the iPad mini,¬†and more, and we talk about them on the show!</p>\n\n\n\n<p>This is episode 915 with <a href=\"https://www.macworld.com/author/karen_haslam\" target=\"_blank\">Karen Haslam</a>, <a href=\"https://www.macworld.com/author/david.price\" target=\"_blank\">David Price</a>, and <a href=\"https://www.macworld.com/author/Roman-Loyola/\" target=\"_blank\">Roman Loyola</a>.¬†</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Watch episode 915 on YouTube</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><div>\n\n</div></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2>Listen to episode 915 on Apple Podcasts</h2>\n\n\n\t\t\n\t\t<div>\n\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t</div>\n\t\t\n\t\t\t\n\n\n<h2></h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Below are the hot takes mentioned on the show.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>A bigger iMac</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>I recently wrote an article about how the <a href=\"https://www.macworld.com/article/2521284/for-the-first-time-ever-you-dont-need-to-be-afraid-to-buy-a-new-mac.html\" target=\"_blank\">Mac lineup is as strong as it‚Äôs ever been</a>, considering the models available and the features offered.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://x.com/stoster1/status/1857505833715720351\">Stoster1 on X posted</a>:</p>\n\n\n<div><figure><a href=\"https://x.com/stoster1/status/1857505833715720351\"><img src=\"https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/stoster1-x-imac.jpg?quality=50&amp;strip=all&amp;w=1200\" alt=\"stoster1 imac X\" srcset=\"https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/stoster1-x-imac.jpg?quality=50&amp;strip=all 2400w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/stoster1-x-imac.jpg?resize=300%2C92&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 300w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/stoster1-x-imac.jpg?resize=768%2C234&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 768w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/stoster1-x-imac.jpg?resize=1200%2C366&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 1200w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/stoster1-x-imac.jpg?resize=1536%2C468&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 1536w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/stoster1-x-imac.jpg?resize=2048%2C625&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 2048w\" width=\"1200\" height=\"366\" loading=\"lazy\" />\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\n\t\t</a></figure><a href=\"https://x.com/stoster1/status/1857505833715720351\" target=\"_blank\">X/stoster1</a></div>\n\n\n\n<p>John Minick said in an email:</p>\n\n\n\n<blockquote>\n<p>Thus far Apple Silicon has been a major disappointment for me.¬†Here is what I wish Apple would produce: A reasonably priced 30-inch iMac with plenty of ports and a high-quality FaceTime camera. Extreme performance is not essential. Drop in an M4 Max from a MacBookPro and Apple would have a computer that I consider purchasing if the price were reasonable.</p>\n<cite>John M. (email)</cite></blockquote>\n\n\n\n<h2>The iPad mini is perfect, even with its imperfections¬†</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Earlier this month, David wrote about how the <a href=\"https://www.macworld.com/article/2532036/the-ipad-mini-is-perfect-except-for-all-the-things-wrong-with-it.html\">iPad mini is a really, really good tablet</a>. Maybe it‚Äôs underappreciated. Roman <a href=\"https://www.macworld.com/article/2504744/ipad-mini-a17-pro-review.html\">reviewed the new iPad mini</a> and like it, too.</p>\n\n\n<div><figure><a href=\"https://x.com/grostad/status/1853849071393591714%20\"><img src=\"https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/grostad-ipad-mini-x.jpg?quality=50&amp;strip=all&amp;w=1200\" alt=\"grostad ipad mini x\" srcset=\"https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/grostad-ipad-mini-x.jpg?quality=50&amp;strip=all 2400w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/grostad-ipad-mini-x.jpg?resize=300%2C76&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 300w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/grostad-ipad-mini-x.jpg?resize=768%2C195&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 768w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/grostad-ipad-mini-x.jpg?resize=1200%2C305&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 1200w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/grostad-ipad-mini-x.jpg?resize=1536%2C390&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 1536w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/grostad-ipad-mini-x.jpg?resize=2048%2C521&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 2048w\" width=\"1200\" height=\"305\" loading=\"lazy\" />\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\n\t\t</a></figure><a href=\"https://x.com/grostad/status/1853849071393591714%20\" target=\"_blank\">X/grostad</a></div>\n\n\n\n<div><div>\n<p>On Facebook, Michael Trapp said:</p>\n\n\n\n<blockquote>\n<p>I love my iPad Mini as my in-car navigation and everything else.. No need for limited CarPlay when I have the FULL IOS available and the screen is pretty much the same size or bigger (except for some ‚Äì Tesla) than most OEM screens. And I can take it¬†from car2car and with me when I park and get out (since it fits in my docker pant pockets).¬†<img height=\"16\" width=\"16\" src=\"https://static.xx.fbcdn.net/images/emoji.php/v9/tf6/2/16/1f609.png\" alt=\"üòâ\" loading=\"lazy\" /></p>\n<cite><a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/Macworld/posts/pfbid02Dkia8df37csuFen36bALYPDRZshWRH8yudJkmZr42Fr4wHpv1MB4TMqCXArvbswPl\">Michael Trapp (Facebook)</a></cite></blockquote>\n</div></div>\n\n\n\n<h2>New Magic Mouse?</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Bloomberg‚Äôs Mark Gurman (subscription required) <a href=\"https://www.bloomberg.com/news/newsletters/2024-12-15/apple-working-on-giant-foldable-ipad-revamped-mouse-longer-range-airtag-2\">reports</a> that Apple is working on a new redesigned Magic Mouse ‚Äúfor the modern era.‚Äù It likely won‚Äôt be ready within the next 12 to 18 months. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><div>\n<blockquote><p>Don‚Äôt fix it. There‚Äôs something very sensual about flipping my mouse and plugging that cable right in.</p>‚Äî <a href=\"https://bsky.app/profile/did:plc:hvakgfbw7apwny2h45tdelee?ref_src=embed\">Joe Daddy (@quetzalcoatl87.bsky.social)</a> <a href=\"https://bsky.app/profile/did:plc:hvakgfbw7apwny2h45tdelee/post/3ldentonmls2o?ref_src=embed\">2024-12-15T20:31:35.955Z</a></blockquote>\n</div></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><div>\n<blockquote><p>Lol they will probably get rid of the charging port all together and make it 100% dependent on wireless charging. And then sell you a wireless charging mousepad.</p>‚Äî <a href=\"https://bsky.app/profile/did:plc:4hew6jcdftxdqm2mbxfhivtq?ref_src=embed\"> (@chrissaiyan.bsky.social)</a> <a href=\"https://bsky.app/profile/did:plc:4hew6jcdftxdqm2mbxfhivtq/post/3ldemprxhu222?ref_src=embed\">2024-12-15T20:11:31.459Z</a></blockquote>\n</div></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><div>\n<blockquote><p>To be honest, if I were Apple, I‚Äôd redesign this, but keep the usb-c port on the bottom because people get irrationally upset about something that needs to be used for 10 minutes every 4 months. You don‚Äôt use the mouse 24/7!</p>‚Äî <a href=\"https://bsky.app/profile/did:plc:yfjaujt3h6t2ezhreepttbo6?ref_src=embed\">Brian Christiansen (@briandigital.com)</a> <a href=\"https://bsky.app/profile/did:plc:yfjaujt3h6t2ezhreepttbo6/post/3lde57sltic22?ref_src=embed\">2024-12-15T15:34:09.134Z</a></blockquote>\n</div></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2>Subscribe to the Macworld Podcast</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>You can subscribe to the Macworld Podcast‚Äîor leave us a review!‚Äî<a href=\"https://itunes.apple.com/us/podcast/id563933198\">right here in the Podcasts app</a>. The Macworld Podcast is also <a href=\"https://open.spotify.com/show/3uyZkE4tjbwNNrJCLsBUAM?si=OdOljEAYQvC_ewEsMfKzXA\">available on Spotify</a> and on the <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/@MacworldPodcast\">Macworld Podcast YouTube channel</a>.¬† Or you can point your favorite podcast-savvy RSS reader at: https://feeds.megaphone.fm/macworld</p>\n\n\n\n<p>To find previous episodes, visit <a href=\"https://www.macworld.com/opinion/podcast\">Macworld‚Äôs podcast page</a> or our home on <a href=\"https://cms.megaphone.fm/channel/macworld\">MegaPhone</a>.</p>\n\n\n<div><figure><a href=\"https://itunes.apple.com/us/podcast/id563933198\"><img src=\"https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/apple-podcasts-badge.jpg?quality=50&amp;strip=all&amp;w=1200\" alt=\"Apple Podcasts badge \" srcset=\"https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/apple-podcasts-badge.jpg?quality=50&amp;strip=all 1300w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/apple-podcasts-badge.jpg?resize=300%2C73&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 300w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/apple-podcasts-badge.jpg?resize=768%2C186&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 768w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/apple-podcasts-badge.jpg?resize=1200%2C291&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 1200w\" width=\"1200\" height=\"291\" loading=\"lazy\" />\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\n\t\t</a></figure><p>Apple</p></div>\n\n</div>","author":"","siteTitle":"Macworld","siteHash":"37e84dd5a21fa961d6d6630e269546024dbb7741b2e2fadbe74f47383c70dfbb","entryHash":"7a2433ae3be0645e94d36529bdcf5ead134812f5915812068e914e6483866455","category":"Apple"}